<P><FONT SIZE=2>On 18/05/10 07:02, Jeff Squyres wrote:<BR>
<BR>
&gt; What's the advantage of /dev/shm?&nbsp; (I don't know anything<BR>
&gt; about /dev/shm)<BR>
<BR>
Looking at our CentOS 5.4 install /dev/shm is a tmpfs<BR>
filesystem (defaults to use up to 1/2 RAM of the system)<BR>
and hence should give lightning fast file I/O.<BR>
<BR>
More info here:<BR>
<BR>
<A HREF="http://wiki.linuxquestions.org/wiki/Tmpfs">http://wiki.linuxquestions.org/wiki/Tmpfs</A><BR>
<BR>
cheers!<BR>
